# Variable naming

Do **not** restate ESLint/Prettier or `yarn fix-code-style` (**code-style**). Do **not** restate the
`t('ai:…')` workflow (**translations**).

**Precedence:** If a bullet disagrees with the file you edit, **match the file** (**Consistency**
below). Defaults for new code only—no drive-by renames.

## Casing

`camelCase` for values/functions; `PascalCase` for components, context providers, enums;
`UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for stable module constants. **`Id`** in camelCase (`clusterId`), not `ID`.

## React

Hooks `use` + `PascalCase`; handlers `handle*`; callback props `on*`. Refs `*Ref`; file-local
subcomponents `PascalCase`. Prefer `handleSubmit`, `onChange`, `isModalOpen` over repeating the
screen in every name; add a qualifier only to disambiguate (`handleSaveDraft` vs `handlePublish`,
`handleClusterCreate` vs `handleClusterUpdate`). `useState`: `[foo, setFoo]`. `isLoading` or
`loading` OK; narrow (e.g. `isInfraEnvLoading`) only when **several** loading flags share a scope.

## Booleans

Prefer `is*`, `has*`, `can*` (`has*` ~ possession/completion, `is*` ~ simple flags). Prefer positive
names; use negative / `isNot*` when the call site reads clearer.

## Redux / async

Match the package (`select*`, `*Async` thunks, existing service names)—no parallel scheme.

## Forms and types

`*Props` (type or interface—do not force one); `*Values` / `*FormValues`. In **`libs/ui-lib/`**,
suffix `Type` / `Values` / `Props` to avoid clashes; elsewhere mirror that package. Schemas:
`*ValidationSchema`, `*Schema`, `get*InitialValues` like existing modules. i18n: **`t`** for
`TFunction` in schema/label factories (see **Single letters**).

## Length

Short domain names (`clusterRows`); plural collections (`hosts`); drop redundant
`List`/`Array`/`Items` when the type implies a collection. Drop scope-duplicated words
(`CreateClusterForm` → `handleSubmit`). Reuse codebase abbreviations (SNO, OCM, VIP); no new opaque
ones. Long logic → named `const` or helper; exported names may be longer, **locals** shorter.

## Consistency

Match dominant style in the file (including hook acronym casing).

## Tests

`create*` + entity (e.g. `createCluster`).

## Single letters

OK: index `i`/`j` with named elements `(row, i)`, `(col, j)`; ignored `_` with index; **`t`** for
`TFunction` in factories; **`e`** in `catch`; generics `T`, `R`, `S`, `K`, `V`, … **Not** for domain
entities—use words; if the file differs, **Consistency** wins.

## Out of scope

No repo-wide renames—**match local** spelling (e.g. `DropDown` vs `Dropdown`). No changing of
existing variable names unless their meaning changes.
